<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="106" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,889,970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">
(
<figureCitation box="[562,639,889,908]" captionStart-0="Figs" captionStart-1="Figs" captionStartId-0="2.[151,190,1530,1549]" captionStartId-1="5.[113,152,1497,1516]" captionTargetBox-0="[215,1063,221,1466]" captionTargetBox-1="[153,1051,209,1447]" captionTargetId-0="figure-10@2.[209,1068,218,1471]" captionTargetId-1="figure-14@5.[149,1053,209,1453]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="Figs. 1-6. 1-3: Amaurosoma longicorne (von Roser, 1840); 4-6: A. bernasconii sp. nov., male, holotype. 1, 4 – abdominal sternites 4 and 5; 2, 5 – surstyli and cerci; 3, 6 – praegonite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 1-2, 4-5); 0.1 mm (Figs. 3, 6)." captionText-1="Figs. 7-11. 7: Amaurosoma bernasconii sp. nov., female, allotype, abdominal sternites 4 to 7. 8-9: Microprosopa ozerovi sp. nov., male, paratype; 10-11: Norellisoma vonickai sp. nov., female. 8 – abdominal sternites 3 to 5; 9 – praegonite; 10 – abdominal sternites 5 to 7; 11 – abdominal sternite 8. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 10); 0.1 mm (Figs. 7, 9, 11)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468111" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468113" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4468111/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4468113/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Figs. 4-7</figureCitation>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,248,923,943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Type material.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[256,339,924,943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
: ♁, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[381,582,923,943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">
<collectingCountry box="[381,579,923,943]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">CZECH REPUBLIC</collectingCountry>
:
</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[590,665,924,943]" country="Czech Republic" name="Jihomoravsky" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">MORAVIA</collectingRegion>
mer., Rokytná near Moravský Krumlov (6963), deciduous forest, 
<date box="[264,351,950,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" value="1986-05-20">20.v.1986</date>
, F. Šifner leg. 
<typeStatus box="[473,554,950,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">ALLOTYPE</typeStatus>
: 
<specimenCount box="[566,582,947,970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, same data as 
<typeStatus box="[705,780,950,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">holotype</typeStatus>
(coll. Šifner).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,993,1594]" box="[113,724,993,1018]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,252,993,1017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Description.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[396,483,993,1017]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4-5 mm</quantity>
, primary colour black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,993,1594]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Head. Posterior portion of head dark and slightly grey dusted, orbits, upper part of parafacialia, and frontal vitta black, a strip in front of frontal vitta yellowish brown, entire antennae black, arista bare, second aristomere slightly prolonged, arista thickened to half of its length, face, lower part of parafacialia and genae yellowish white, palpi yellow without distinct hair bristles. Vibrissal callus with two bristles and one short bristle between them.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,993,1594]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Thorax. Acrostichal bristles very sparse or almost absent, two scutellar bristles very long at their midlength arched outside, other chaetotaxy standard. All legs yellow, fore femora without short bristles at inner side, wings hyaline, all veins distinct and dark.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,993,1594]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">
Abdomen. Male – sternite 3 narrow and long, sternite 4 rectangular and slightly narrowed proximally, lobes of sternite 5 straight, with short bristles medially (
<figureCitation box="[863,931,1314,1338]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[151,190,1530,1549]" captionTargetBox="[215,1063,221,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[209,1068,218,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1-6. 1-3: Amaurosoma longicorne (von Roser, 1840); 4-6: A. bernasconii sp. nov., male, holotype. 1, 4 – abdominal sternites 4 and 5; 2, 5 – surstyli and cerci; 3, 6 – praegonite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 1-2, 4-5); 0.1 mm (Figs. 3, 6)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468111/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), surstyli only slightly arched, at inner side with bristles, cerci short and narrow (
<figureCitation box="[807,871,1345,1370]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[151,190,1530,1549]" captionTargetBox="[215,1063,221,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[209,1068,218,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1-6. 1-3: Amaurosoma longicorne (von Roser, 1840); 4-6: A. bernasconii sp. nov., male, holotype. 1, 4 – abdominal sternites 4 and 5; 2, 5 – surstyli and cerci; 3, 6 – praegonite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 1-2, 4-5); 0.1 mm (Figs. 3, 6)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468111/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), praegonite narrow, slightly arched apically with one long, almost perpendicular, lateral bristle (
<figureCitation box="[924,990,1378,1402]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[151,190,1530,1549]" captionTargetBox="[215,1063,221,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[209,1068,218,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1-6. 1-3: Amaurosoma longicorne (von Roser, 1840); 4-6: A. bernasconii sp. nov., male, holotype. 1, 4 – abdominal sternites 4 and 5; 2, 5 – surstyli and cerci; 3, 6 – praegonite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 1-2, 4-5); 0.1 mm (Figs. 3, 6)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468111/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Female – sternites 4-6 long and rectangular, without distinct bristles, sternite 7 oval, wide, with an incision and four bristles caudally, sternites 8 small and pointed caudally (
<figureCitation box="[903,969,1442,1466]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[113,152,1497,1516]" captionTargetBox="[153,1051,209,1447]" captionTargetId="figure-14@5.[149,1053,209,1453]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 7-11. 7: Amaurosoma bernasconii sp. nov., female, allotype, abdominal sternites 4 to 7. 8-9: Microprosopa ozerovi sp. nov., male, paratype; 10-11: Norellisoma vonickai sp. nov., female. 8 – abdominal sternites 3 to 5; 9 – praegonite; 10 – abdominal sternites 5 to 7; 11 – abdominal sternite 8. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 10); 0.1 mm (Figs. 7, 9, 11)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468113/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,993,1594]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1127,219,371]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,400,1473,1497]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Šifner, 2008" authorityName="Šifner" authorityYear="2008" box="[410,689,1475,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Amaurosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernasconii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[410,689,1475,1498]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Amaurosoma bernasconii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[700,787,1474,1497]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the related 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Amaurosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevifrons">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">A. brevifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the following characters: 
<taxonomicName authority="Šifner, 2008" authorityName="Šifner" authorityYear="2008" box="[530,686,1506,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Amaurosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernasconii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[530,546,1507,1530]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[560,686,1507,1530]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">bernasconii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[693,776,1506,1529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
– male: abdominal sternite 4 rectangular, praegonite with one long, almost perpendicular, lateral bristle; female: abdominal sternite 7 oval with caudal incision (
<figureCitation box="[505,605,1570,1594]" captionStart-0="Figs" captionStart-1="Figs" captionStartId-0="2.[151,190,1530,1549]" captionStartId-1="5.[113,152,1497,1516]" captionTargetBox-0="[215,1063,221,1466]" captionTargetBox-1="[153,1051,209,1447]" captionTargetId-0="figure-10@2.[209,1068,218,1471]" captionTargetId-1="figure-14@5.[149,1053,209,1453]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="Figs. 1-6. 1-3: Amaurosoma longicorne (von Roser, 1840); 4-6: A. bernasconii sp. nov., male, holotype. 1, 4 – abdominal sternites 4 and 5; 2, 5 – surstyli and cerci; 3, 6 – praegonite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 1-2, 4-5); 0.1 mm (Figs. 3, 6)." captionText-1="Figs. 7-11. 7: Amaurosoma bernasconii sp. nov., female, allotype, abdominal sternites 4 to 7. 8-9: Microprosopa ozerovi sp. nov., male, paratype; 10-11: Norellisoma vonickai sp. nov., female. 8 – abdominal sternites 3 to 5; 9 – praegonite; 10 – abdominal sternites 5 to 7; 11 – abdominal sternite 8. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 10); 0.1 mm (Figs. 7, 9, 11)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468111" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468113" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4468111/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4468113/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Figs. 4-7</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[625,881,1571,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Amaurosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevifrons">
<emphasis box="[625,881,1571,1594]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Amaurosoma brevifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– male: abdominal sternite 4 oval, praegonite with two short bristles; female: abdominal sternite 7 oval, without incision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
